            "uuid": "98a2c5ab-2f3c-42c9-b6a5-277e4027e6fc",
            "title": "Abbas & The Flap of a Butterfly Wing. ğŸ˜¯",
            "slug": "hushpuppy_dog_wolf",
            "html": "<hr><p>How a nation metamorphosed from Hush-puppy to Hush-Dog to Hush-Wolf in lawlessness. And the little daily actions that make large changes in the wealth of people, companies &amp; nations!</p><blockquote>A country is in for trouble when its ruler is childish, and its leaders party all day long.<br></blockquote><h2 id=\"dec-2009\">Dec. 2009 </h2><p>At 5:00 am, a teenage boy of 17 Years, visibly shaken rushes his sister to the hospital. She was in perilous pain and coughing thick pale blood clots. In the last few months, she had repeated excruciating pain in the abdomen. However, in the last 5 days, the pains had intensified with an inability to sleep, and intermittent drowsiness. As she sat sprawled on a maligned bench, her bones were visible across her now whitish skin.<br>At the Gbagada Hospital, very few people roamed the lobby. The nurse on duty had requested a registration fee before admission. The amount required was a paltry 1,000 NGN (2.3 USD). The teenager had braced this fear to make a last-ditch effort to save her life at the hospital. His sister had resisted being brought to the hospital. Hope and despair had been the fortitude for his action; hope that a good Samaritan would chance by, and despair that there is a chance she could be snatched from the feet of the grim-reaper.<br>Born and inherited from a lineage of poverty, they could barely afford a meal daily. Less the cost of registration. All alternatives administered to herâ€Šâ€”â€ŠLocal Herbs, Prayers &amp; Fasting, Self medications and anticipating a miracle, exacerbated the pain and worsened her state.<br>Their dad, an attendant in an eatery, had been owed six months of wages. Their mom, a local â€˜ogi &amp; akamu sellerâ€™, had borrowed so much from the neighbors that, doors were slammed shut at the sight of her. The family owed everyone in the neighborhood, including the local â€˜olo deâ€™ (security man) with whom they lent the money for the â€˜okada rideâ€™ to the Gbagada hospital. <br>The young boy, alone and red-eyed in tears, begged, pleaded, and wailed that his sister be attended to. She was losing pulse and it was unsure how long she would last. <br>The Nurse, looking in sympathy at an almost lifeless sister, was out of options. Just last week, she received a query and fine for attending to a patient who had left without clearing their bills. Now she was going to paying the bills spread over six months. It stung her that a good intention would reduce her meager take home and a red in her file. And she vowed never to make a second trip to the â€˜good Samaritan laneâ€™ ever! She insistedâ€Šâ€”â€Šâ€˜No Money, No treatmentâ€™. <br>Now his wails were beginning to awake a few patients. The physician on duty had also rung the reception demanding that order be restored! As the pandemonium of his cries escalated into a scene, the security men were called in to whisk his sickly lifeless sister and himself off the premises of the hospital.<br>Then a middle-aged woman walked in. She had come in earlier than expected for a routine check-up. Listening to his story, she told the nurse to put the bills on her on file. This good samaritan was indeed God-sent. Prayers Answered!<br>5 hours since she was brought in, and two hours since she was whisked into the operating room, there was still no word from the operating theater. His mother had arrived then. There, they sat, hands held together in prayers, awaiting the news of a successful operation. <br>A few minutes later, clandestinely, the doctor walked in. He apologized and explained <em>in hush tones </em>â€˜We tried all we could. She had lost too much blood. The malignant growth had eaten her organs. I am sorry, but your daughter did not make it!.â€™ The coursing of a thousand cries between mother and brother ripped several reverberations across the hospital. <br>That day, he vowed that he would never forgive himself for the poverty of his family in a nation so wretched to be a citizen of!</p><hr><h2 id=\"june-1961-\">June. 1961. </h2><p>Ed Lorenz, a meteorologist &amp; mathematician, was using a simple digital computer to simulate weather patterns. He configured 12 modeling variables (equations) representing atmospheric elements like Wind, Temperature, and Speed. After the initial experiment, he wanted to repeat the sequence of data. And so made the intuitive decision to start in the middle of its course.<br>He entered a printout of the data corresponding to the middle of the original simulation. Alas, the machine printed numbers completely misaligned to the previous calculation. <br>His fortuitous Error: the rounded decimal in the computer printout. His computer worked with 6 digit precision. However, his printout rounded the variables into 3 digit-numbers. The difference between the computer output (0.506127) and the paper printout (0.506) was tiny and hence should have no practical effect as the consensus was at the time. <br>However, he discovered that small differences in the initial states of complex systems can lead to massive differences. Prof. Ed determined that this small change in initial conditions, which lead to a large change in long-term outcomes, be called Â <em>Sensitive Dependence on initial conditions</em>. <br>His work would go on to open a new field in Quantum Physics and earn him the Kyoto Prize (Japanâ€™s highest private award for lifetime achievement in the arts and sciences)for basic sciences almost 3 decades later.</p><hr><h2 id=\"feb-2nd-2020-\">Feb 2nd 2020.</h2><blockquote>News Flash: Davido''s Brother has a luxury wedding in Dubai as HushPuppy Sprays rolls of Hundred Dollar Notes. </blockquote><p>In his home country, he was born with an unmissable inheritance; poverty. The struggles of his parents and their inability to cater for his siblings ; the death of his sister because of a lack of 1000; his hard work and the challenges he had faced gaining education or the pursuit of happiness; culminated in his decision to leave <em>Naija </em>for â€˜greener pastures.â€™ <br>Born into hardship, shaped by struggles and succeeding by determination, hook or crook. His sojourn into foreign land had proved fortuitous. He had now taken residence first at Malaysia and most recently, the United Arab Emirates. Albeit successfully. <br>He was an internet celebrity known for his lavish lifestyle. He lived at Palazzo Versace, a quite expensive &amp; super-luxurious hotel in Dubai. His IG handle is stuffed to suffocation with exquisite and expensive items; super-luxury cars, top range designer labels, expensive watches, top of the range clothes, bling-bling, and items of rare quality. <br>In fact, he had the moniker, â€˜ the Billionaire Gucci Masterâ€™ on one of his social handles. Who would argue the billionaire status? He had escaped the â€˜Nigerian Struggleâ€™ to live â€˜The Gucci Lifeâ€™. Even the Nigeria elite reveled in his popularity. He hobnobbed with super-celebrities; being one in his own right with a verified Instagram account and 2.5 million followers. His Instagram giveaways were unrivaled, having his followers wait on his every post like the man at the pool of Bethesda; usually in hundred dollar bills. His likes &amp; comments per post could reach as much as 200kâ€Šâ€”â€Ša 9% click-through rate.<br>Whatâ€™s more, he was acknowledged for his patronage with designer labels. On his birthday, October, 11, one of the top-notch designer labels, Fendi, sent a massive cake with his picture and various products shopping bags carved into the cake. <em>He had made his money as a Real Estate Developer investing across multiple countries and in various income-producing assets. </em>Ray Hushppuppi was now living â€˜La Vida Locaâ€™ (The Rich Crazy Life).</p><hr><h2 id=\"dec-29-1972-\">Dec 29. 1972.</h2><p>Professor Lorenzo went on to present his finding to his colleagues. He was scorned. His paper, presented to the American Association for the Advancement of Science was titled; <em>Predictability: Does the flap of a butterflyâ€™s wings in Brazil set off a tornado in Texas?</em><br>In the paper, he explained that minuscule disturbances neither increase nor decrease the frequency of various weather patterns. However, they could modify the sequence in which these events occur. He asked the question then that â€˜<em>Is the behavior of the atmosphere unstable with respect to perturbations of small amplitude?â€™ </em>In giving an answer, he theorized that the inability to predict accurately weather patterns sufficiently in a distant future time is based on how small perturbations that can lead to complex changes in weather patterns. He penned a few conclusions: <br>1. Small errors in the coarser structure of weather patternsâ€Šâ€”â€Štend to double every three days. <br>2. Small errors in the finer structure tend to grow more rapidly, doubling in hours or less. <br>3. Errors in the finer structure (1) having attained appreciable size, tend to induce errors in the coarser structure (2). <br>4. Certain special weather quantitiesâ€Šâ€”â€Šlike weekly average temperature or total rainfallâ€Šâ€”â€Šmay be predictable at a range at which entire weather patterns are not. <br>Prof Lorenzo concluded in his paper that although the original question â€˜Doest the Flap of a butterfly wing in Brazil cause a Tornado in Texasâ€™â€Šâ€”â€Šwas still unanswered, it is maintained that the atmosphere is unstable because of finer &amp; coarser structure in atmospheric elementâ€Šâ€”â€Šincluding the flap of a butterfly!</p><hr><h2 id=\"july-3-2020\">July 3, 2020</h2><p><em> â€˜Ramon Olorunwa Abbas, 37, a.k.a. â€œRay Hushpuppiâ€ and â€œHush,â€ a Nigerian national, arrived in Chicago Thursday evening after being expelled from the United Arab Emirates (UAE)â€™ </em>reads a complaint from the Department of Justice, US Attorneyâ€™s office for the Central district of California. <br>On the 24th of June, the FBI &amp; Interpol had raided Hushpuppi and his gang in a sting called <em>Operation Fox Hunt 2 </em>. More than $41 million in cash, 13 luxury cars worth $6.8 million, 21 computer devices, 47 smartphones, 15 memory sticks, five Hard Drives containing 119,859 files and addresses of 1,926,400 victims were confiscated. He was arrested along with 11 other African cyber criminals. It was alleged that they had defrauded almost 2 million victims. <br>The FBI &amp; Interpol corporation as well as the Dubai Police planned the operation, flawlessly. The complaint filed on the department of justice affirmed that he had been tracked using social media; namely email, IG, and Snapchat accounts. His flamboyancy left a trail of evidence that was used to link him to the alleged crime. He was arrested and extradited to the United States. He had engaged in BECâ€Šâ€”â€ŠBusiness Email Compromiseâ€Šâ€”â€ŠFraud schemes that had targeted a Â New York Law Firm, an English Premier Soccer club and a Foreign Bank. <br>His hearing comes up July 21, 2020.</p><hr><h2 id=\"july-15-2020\">July 15, 2020</h2><p>While we know, as Dr. Lorenzo observed, that the flap of a butterfly wing might not set up a tornado in Texas, at least not to what was observed. We understand that the results of those little decisions would affect the overall outcome, for the weather pattern and the path of tornados. <br>Is there a way the butterfly would have flapped itsâ€™ wing on that fateful day when Ray brought his sister to the hospital?</p><ul><li>Ifâ€Šâ€”â€Šby the flap of the butterflyâ€Šâ€”â€Šthat Nurse on that fateful day ignored her bossesâ€™ insensitivity and admitted young Abbasâ€™s sister, would she have lived?</li><li>Ifâ€Šâ€”â€Šby the flap of the butterflyâ€Šâ€”â€Šthe hospital put in place a policy that honors the Hippocratic oath that their first duty was to save lives, would she have lived?</li><li>Ifâ€Šâ€”â€Šby the flap of the butterflyâ€Šâ€”â€Šyoung Abbasâ€™s parents created a small nest-egg, no matter how small, earlier in their marriage, and to be used only for emergency, would she be alive?</li><li>Ifâ€Šâ€”â€Šby the flap of the butterflyâ€Šâ€”â€Šthe government of Nigeria initiated Medicare for all citizens that ensure citizens have access to credible health services, would she have lived?</li><li>Ifâ€Šâ€”â€Šby the flap of the butterflyâ€Šâ€”â€Š the employer who owed Abbasâ€™s father paid him the six months owed him. Would she have lived?</li></ul><p>Would the outcomes of these small changes in the initial conditions that led to her death been altered? The butterfly effect considers little actions taken daily, in insignificant and negligible amounts that seem to be of no immediate consequence. Would it have influenced Abbasâ€™s decision to vow out of poverty whatever it takes, his decision to be involved in alleged BEC fraud, his arrest as a co-conspirator, and the global negative outlook for Nigeria!</p><p>And that is our one goal at InvestNairaâ€Šâ€”â€ŠThe Financial Butterfly Effect. That one naira saved today, seemingly insignificant, would make the difference tomorrow. The quality of life you live. The quality of life afforded your family. The quality of growth and development of our dear country Nigeria!</p><p>Yes, 1 naira is insignificant, but it can alter the sensitivity dependence on the initial conditions of the status quo of poverty palpable in this nation. And maybe a mirror reflection of your background!</p><p>Do you think your 1 naira saved today could birth the first trillion-dollar company in Africa tomorrow and enrich your generation thereby?</p><p>We build for so!</p><p>That is what InvestNaira is aboutâ€Šâ€”â€Šthe flap of a butterfly wing, saving, investing, and growing wealth on a minuscule lever. That insignificant attitude might cause a tornado in the growth and development of Africa, a few decades in!</p><p>Join the Financial Buttery Fly Effect challenge today!</p><hr><p> </p><h2 id=\"october-11-2030-\">October 11, 2030.</h2><p><em>â€œToday, he is known as the first centi-billionaire tech founder. Ramon Abbas, who turns 47 today, has defied the odds of poverty, squalor and a corrupt society as a role model &amp; a shining example of the Nigeria Visionâ€Šâ€”â€Šthat change begins with tiny, minuscule steps taken repeatedly on an individual basis that affects the national outcome. Â Forbes estimates his net worth at $15 Billion, making him the 10th richest man in Nigeria and the youngest of the pack.</em>â€ Forbes Featurette.</p><p>What if Ramon had taken an alternative route to wealth? What if he had vowed to get a good education, build wealth steadily, and never give up, no matter what? Would that decision have made him wealthy? Maybe not?<br>However, that decision would put him in the path of building an empire like Bezos (Amazon), Page &amp; Brien (Google), or Gates (Microsoft). Each of their companies have a Market capitalization of more than 1 trillion USD. (1,000,000,000,000 USD = 450,000,000,000,000 NGN)</p><ul><li>Would the flap of that butterfly wingâ€Šâ€”â€Ša decision to build wealth steadily, for the long termâ€Šâ€”â€Šalter the trajectory of technology companies in Africa</li><li>Would the flap of a butterfly wing 10 years ago on his sisterâ€™s death help shape him to be Nigeriaâ€™s first true Statemen since Democracy in 1999?</li><li>Would that flap of a butterfly wings see him feature in a CNN Africa Voicer or a BBC Documentary for his exploits as a Nigerian in United Arab Emirates?</li><li>Would the culmination of these decisions land him a primetime sport on Oprah Winfreyâ€™s show rather than investigated by the US Attorneyâ€™s Office?</li></ul><p>We can only build, a butterfly flap a time, to effect a change!</p><p>Join us today! One butterfly flapper time and letâ€™s build wealth steadily. For Individual. For Company. For Nation.</p><hr><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-width-full kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/900/0*HOMssOrbXJ0X0BOl\" class=\"kg-image\"><figcaption>Join Us!</figcaption></figure><hr><blockquote><strong>Sources</strong><br><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Butterfly_effect\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Butterfly_effect</a><br><a href=\"http://eaps4.mit.edu/research/Lorenz/Butterfly_1972.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">http://eaps4.mit.edu/research/Lorenz/Butterfly_1972.pdf</a><br><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fDek6cYijxI\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fDek6cYijxI</a><br><a href=\"https://edition.cnn.com/2020/07/12/us/ray-hushpuppi-alleged-money-laundering-trnd/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://edition.cnn.com/2020/07/12/us/ray-hushpuppi-alleged-money-laundering-trnd/index.html</a><br><a href=\"https://www.justice.gov/usao-cdca/pr/nigerian-national-brought-us-face-charges-conspiring-launder-hundreds-millions-dollars\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://www.justice.gov/usao-cdca/pr/nigerian-national-brought-us-face-charges-conspiring-launder-hundreds-millions-dollars</a><br><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/126070364137174/posts/3126225064121674/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://www.facebook.com/126070364137174/posts/3126225064121674/</a><br><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V29eGDH-nM0\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V29eGDH-nM0</a></blockquote><blockquote><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vkQEqXAz44I\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vkQEqXAz44I</a></blockquote>",
