            "slug": "monkey-business",
            "html": "<p>The Legend behind All Greedy Money Schemes</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/900/1*xXdTo1oUlL9ppN5EIVofLw.png\" class=\"kg-image\"><figcaption>The Monkey Business!</figcaption></figure><p>Once upon a time, a lot of monkeys lived near a village.ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’<br>One day a merchant came to the village to buy these monkeys! He announced that he will be buying monkeys at $100 each.</p><blockquote><strong>IN Anecdote</strong>: Price is what you pay, value is what you get. Anyone can make s#*&amp;^t valuable buy asking <strong>mugu-magas </strong>to pay premium for a special breed &amp; blend.</blockquote><p>The villagers thought the man insane.ğŸ˜‡ They thought how can somebody buy stray monkeys at $100 each?<br>Still, some people caught some monkeys and gave it to this merchant and he gave them $100 for each monkey.</p><blockquote><strong>IN Anecdote</strong>: The Audacity of a snake oil salesman is all it takes to swing people into believing in nothingness. Beware! Flashy Lifestyles. Flashy Rides. Flashy Blings.FLashy Bank Account. Flashy social media pages.</blockquote><p>This news spread like wildfire and people caught monkeys and sold it to the merchant.ğŸ˜¬</p><blockquote><strong>IN Anecdote:</strong> The virality factor of any Monkey Businessâ€Šâ€”â€ŠMoney Spining Schemeâ€Šâ€”â€Šis multiplied by the use of Social Media. Bank Alert Screen-Shots, A testimony from one neighbor to another, is all it takes to light the wild-fire. Envy in matters of money, is g.o.d!</blockquote><p>After a few days, the merchant announced that he will now buy monkeys at $200 each. The lazy villagers also ran around to catch the remaining monkeys! They sold the remaining monkeys at $200 each.ğŸ˜‹</p><p>Then the merchant announced that he will again buy monkeys at $500 each!<br>ğŸ˜®ğŸ’µğŸ’µğŸ’µğŸ’µğŸ’µ</p><p>The villagers start to lose sleep! â€¦ They caught six or seven monkeys, which was all that was left and got $500 each.ğŸ™ŠğŸµğŸµğŸµğŸµğŸµğŸ’</p><blockquote><strong>IN Anecdote: </strong>A trial is always what convinces orders to go in. If someone has PHedâ€Šâ€”â€Šprovided helpâ€Šâ€”â€Šand GHedâ€Šâ€”â€ŠGot Help, thatâ€™s all. Everyone follows in, lemin like.)</blockquote><p>The villagers were waiting anxiously for the next announcement.</p><p>Then the merchant announced that he is going home for a week. And when he returns, he will buy monkeys at $1000 each!ğŸµ</p><blockquote><strong><em>IN Anecdote</em></strong><em>: If itâ€™s too good to be true, itâ€™s always too true to be good!</em></blockquote><p>He asked his employee to take care of the monkeys he bought. He was alone taking care of all the monkeys in a cage.ğŸ¤ ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’ğŸ’</p><p>The merchant went home.ğŸ˜</p><p>The villagers were very sad as there were no more monkeys left for them to sell it at $1000 each.â˜¹ğŸ˜ğŸ˜“</p><p>Then the employee told them that he will sell some monkeys at $700 each secretly. ğŸ˜¶</p><p>This news spread like fire. Since the merchant will buy monkeys at $1000 each whenever he returns, it means there is a $300 profit for each monkey.ğŸ˜¬</p><p>The next day, villagers made a queue near the monkey ğŸ’ğŸ¤‘</p><p>The employee sold all the monkeys at $700 each. The rich bought monkeys in big lots. The poor borrowed money from money lenders and also bought monkeys!ğŸ’ğŸ’µ</p><blockquote><strong>IN Anecdote: </strong>But godliness with contentment is great gain.</blockquote><p>The villagers took care of their monkeys &amp; waited for the merchant to return. But nobody came! â€¦ğŸ˜¤ Then they ran to the employeeâ€¦ğŸ¤ <br>But he had already left too !ğŸ˜‰</p><p>The villagers then realized that they have bought the useless stray monkeys at $700 each and unable to sell them! ğŸ˜©ğŸ˜«ğŸ˜¨ğŸ˜°ğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­.</p><blockquote><strong><em>IN Anecdotes: </em></strong><em>The greater fool theory states that the price of an object is determined not by its intrinsic value, but rather by irrational beliefs and expectations of market participants.</em></blockquote><p>Stay out of the next monkey ğŸ™ˆğŸ™‰ğŸ™Š business. Monkey Businesses bankrupt a lot of people and make a few people filthy rich.</p><p>This is the story of All Greedy Schemes offering unsustainable returns every few days. However, enduring <a href=\"http://InvestNaira.com\" rel=\"noopener\">Wealth is built daily</a>, consistently, shrewdly and poco-a-poco.</p><p><a href=\"http://InvestNaira.com\" rel=\"noopener\">Start Here, for the Long Term</a>!</p><p>Have you had any monkey business experience? Kindly share.</p><p>(Adapted from internet humor)</p><hr><p>Save | Invest | No Monkey Business Returns!</p><p>Follow us on all Social Media @<a href=\"https://medium.com/u/2da0e019decd\">InvestNaira</a></p>",
