            "id": "5e09bbef4bb28512a342c468",
            "uuid": "b0969302-01ec-4392-a5e1-0a80917670b1",
            "title": "The Short Term is 3 Years.",
            "slug": "three-years-shortterm",
            "html": "<blockquote>For three years itâ€™s fruits will be off-limits to you; it must not be eaten â€” Adon Olam.</blockquote><p>If you set goals, the First Quarter of the year usually is a snap. We are disillusioned by the goals we have projected for the year. We write some daring targets, only to be stymied by various headwinds against their accomplishments. Itâ€™s like having an iPhone X goal and finding yourself with a Sagem-V55 device after the first 90 days.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://nairasense.investnaira.com/content/images/2020/07/image-5.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><p>The iPhone is what we life should look like when we set them goals on Jan 1, 2020. The Sagem V-55 is what life looks like at the end of the second quarter of 2020. Oh, to New Year resolutions without daily actions!!!</p><p>Well, do not give up just yet on those goals. Dreams without discipline and commitment would end as an illusion. It is important always to take disciplined consistent daily actions to achieve our long-term objectives. And that is what we do every single day at InvestNaira. For if you take <em><em>daily disciplined committed </em></em>steps, your iPhone might as well be the Ipone Xr. Far beyond what you can ask, think or imagine!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://nairasense.investnaira.com/content/images/2020/07/image-4.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><p><strong><strong>3 Years is the Short Term.</strong></strong></p><p>30 years ago, we sent mail (courier) once a month.<br>20 years ago, we sent an e-mail once a day.<br>10 years ago, we posted on social media once an hour.<br>Today, we chat with social tools every minute.</p><p>In the social media world of communication, a day is too long a time to wait to get a response. For communication, we can deduce, the short term is a second; the Medium-term is a Minute; the Long Term is an hour. An hour is now eons ago! Choi.</p><p>In building a Financial ark however, we must not use as a yardstick, the disruption of communication via the medium of technology. Rather, the age-old principle of seed-time &amp; harvest remains on the earth. A baby is delivered after 36 weeks in the womb. Shortening a babyâ€™s life cycle might cause deformity. It is against the seed-time and harvest cycle.</p><blockquote><em><em><strong><strong>â€˜You Canâ€™t</strong></strong> Produce a <strong><strong>Baby</strong></strong> in One <strong><strong>Month by Getting Nine Women Pregnant</strong></strong></em></em></blockquote><p>Letâ€™s cue in the agricultural life cycle. Annual crops produce fruits within a year. And you have to replant them yearly, season by season. Perennial crops, however, produce fruits that could span years after their first fruits harvest. Think Cocoa â€” it takes between 3 to 5 year for its first fruits. Or Palm Tree â€” it takes 4 to 6 years for its first fruits. The difference, though, between annual and perennial crops lie in the fruits. Once the perennial crop yields itâ€™s first fruits, they re-produce for decades. We want to plant financial seeds that produce for decades and generations.</p><p><strong><strong>OUR RETURNS Q1</strong></strong></p><p>Returns at Q1 are given below for the various funds.</p><blockquote><em><em>For three years itâ€™s fruits will be off-limits to you; it must not be eaten.</em></em></blockquote><p>In the world of Finance, the value of assets fluctuate as the waves of the sea. Our holding an asset for multiple quarters means they are not liquidated at quarterâ€™s end. This, therefore, means the values of assets would move like the waves of the sea in positive or negative directions. If we stay with the right asset, then we expect more upside than downside. Our challenge in building a financial ark is catching the right asset and sticking with it as it fluctuates. For, the longer we stick in the right direction, the greater the returns.</p><p><strong><strong>INCH BY INCH</strong></strong></p><p>Itâ€™s has been whipped one time too many that Rome was not built in a day. But may we add, there was not a day that Rome was not built.</p><p><em><em><strong><strong>Yard by Yard. Lifeâ€™s Hard. Inch by Inch, everything is a cinch.</strong></strong></em></em></p><p>If we looked at the goal on the first day of the first year, building a financial ark was hardddd. Daringly so! Ask the foremost ark builder, Father Noah. But as we faced down, hands to the spindle, browbeaten and never giving in, <em><em>still we rise! </em></em>Against odds, lots &amp; slots, we rose and advanced. Our mantra, inch by inch, day by passing day, with you, the financial ark becomes a cinch!</p><p>Dear INer, this is our submission to you. Your journey with us on the short term is a three-year commitment of consistent daily discipline of saving. For it is that perennial perspective that yields the first fruits of the results of many decades.</p><p>For, after 3 years, the seeds of our inch-by-inch stance might begin to produce. Then, the assurance of our shared vision and the substance of the hoped-for-future has turned word to flesh!</p><p>Our short term view is the three-year mark. The three year time-frame lies the seed of the 8th wonder of the world â€” compound wealth.</p><hr><p>Save | Invest | Don''t-Pluck.</p>",
